 in this book, based on Mikhail Bakhtin's work, traces the search for common and specific grounds of the humanities, beginning with psychologism through hermeneutics and semiotics up to the present state of self-annihilation. As an alternative, the book seeks to define humanities as the examination of relationships, which offers an array of refreshing perspectives on each field discussed.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aBakhtin dialogics. 4adialogic interculturality. 4adialogic post-modernity. 4adialogical design. 4adialogical philosophy. 4adialogical psychology. 4adialogical sociology. 4adialogicity of epochs. 4aefforts to unite the humanities. 4ahistory of ideas. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Comparative Literature.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2018z978311068818440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618117397423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618117397.jpg  a978-3-11-068818-4  ASP eBook Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG